pecified parameters: `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`, `mincov=4`, `treatment=c(0, 0, 1, 1)`, and `assembly='mock_v1'.\\n4. Use `unite` to combine the datasets into a single methylBase object with `min.per.group=1` and `destrand=FALSE`.\\n5. Save the united methylBase object to `output/mk_united.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n6. Create a summary statistics data frame with the specified columns and save it to `output/unite_stats.tsv` using `write.table`.\\n7. Verify the existence of `output/unite_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (706 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_KxLTKDyQh7Bn6ybyMRWXZDAK"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gMGUz0FudUcP88igRIat5150", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov',\\n                  'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\ntreatment <- c(0, 0, 1, 1)\\n\\n# Load data\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list, \\n                   pipeline = 'bismarkCoverage', \\n                   mincov = 4, \\n                   treatment = treatment, \\n                   assembly = 'mock_v1')\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group = 1, destrand = FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, file = 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Create and save the summary statistics\\ndb_path <- NA\\nunite_stats <- data.frame(n_samples = length(mk_raw),\\n                          n_sites = nrow(mk_united),\\n                          min_per_group = 1,\\n                          destrand = FALSE,\\n                          use_db = FALSE,\\n                          db_path = db_path)\\nwrite.table(unite_stats, file = 'output/unite_stats.tsv', sep = '\\\\t', row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDuplicated, aperm, append, as.data.frame, basename, cbind,\n    colnames, dirname, do.call, duplicated, eval, evalq, Filter, Find,\n    get, grep, grepl, is.unsorted, lapply, Map, mapply, match, mget,\n    order, paste, pmax, pmax.int, pmin, pmin.int, Position, rank,\n    rbind, Reduce, rownames, sapply, saveRDS, table, tapply, unique,\n    unsplit, which.max, which.min\n\nLoading required package: S4Vectors\n\nAttaching package: \u2018S4Vectors\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:utils\u2019:\n\n    findMatches\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    expand.grid, I, unname\n\nLoading required package: IRanges\nLoading required package: GenomeInfoDb\nReceived list of locations.\nError in if (is.na(treatment)) stop(\"Treatment vector is missing.\") : \n  the condition has length > 1\nCalls: methRead -> methRead\nExecution halted\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_gMGUz0FudUcP88igRIat5150"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_PHVvqbz99ULgdtMO2DAh7P42", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleA.bismark.cov\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "too