mark.cov`,\n`sampleD.bismark.cov` \u2014 tab-separated without headers, columns\n`(chrom, start, end, methylation_pct, count_methylated, count_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_KxLTKDyQh7Bn6ybyMRWXZDAK", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R package `methylKit`.\\n2. Define the file paths for the input bismark coverage files.\\n3. Use `methRead` to read the coverage files with the specified parameters: `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`, `mincov=4`, `treatment=c(0, 0, 1, 1)`, and `assembly='mock_v1'.\\n4. Use `unite` to combine the datasets into a single methylBase object with `min.per.group=1` and `destrand=FALSE`.\\n5. Save the united methylBase object to `output/mk_united.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n6. Create a summary statistics data frame with the specified columns and save it to `output/unite_stats.tsv` using `write.table`.\\n7. Verify the existence of `output/unite_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (706 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_KxLTKDyQh7Bn6ybyMRWXZDAK"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gMGUz0FudUcP88igRIat5150", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov',\\n                  'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\ntreatment <- c(0, 0, 1, 1)\\n\\n# Load data\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list, \\n                   pipeline = 'bismarkCoverage', \\n                   mincov = 4, \\n                   treatment = treatment, \\n                   assembly = 'mock_v1')\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group = 1, destrand = FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, file = 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Create and save the summary statistics\\ndb_path <- NA\\nunite_stats <- data.frame(n_samples = length(mk_raw),\\n                          n_sites = nrow(mk_united),\\n                          min_per_group = 1,\\n                          destrand = FALSE,\\n                          use_db = FALSE,\\n                          db_path = db_path)\\nwrite.table(unite_stats, file = 'output/unite_stats.tsv', sep = '\\\\t', row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"rol