,\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_KxLTKDyQh7Bn6ybyMRWXZDAK", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R package `methylKit`.\\n2. Define the file paths for the input bismark coverage files.\\n3. Use `methRead` to read the coverage files with the specified parameters: `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`, `mincov=4`, `treatment=c(0, 0, 1, 1)`, and `assembly='mock_v1'.\\n4. Use `unite` to combine the datasets into a single methylBase object with `min.per.group=1` and `destrand=FALSE`.\\n5. Save the united methylBase object to `output/mk_united.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n6. Create a summary statistics data frame with the specified columns and save it to `output/unite_stats.tsv` using `write.table`.\\n7. Verify the existence of `output/unite_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (706 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_KxLTKDyQh7Bn6ybyMRWXZDAK"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gMGUz0FudUcP88igRIat5150", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov',\\n                 